Package controller

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Command
    Command interface.
    State
    State interface.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractCommand
    AbstractCommand abstract class, implementing ICommand interface, extended by commands Contains a delivery, a delivery round and a graph
    AddDeliveryCommand
    Command that adds a delivery to a delivery round Extends AbstractCommand abstract class Contains a typical day and a second delivery
    AdditionState
    State set when the user clicks on AddDeliveryButton Extends DefaultState abstract class
    CityMapState
    State set when the user has load the map and leaved when the user load the deliveries file Extends DefaultState abstract class
    CommandsList
    CommandList class, contains a list of executed commands Facilitates undo/redo implementation
    Controller
    Controller class, contains methods to manage data Contains a map of the city, a typical day, a graph, a command list, the current state, the window And an instance of each possible state
    DefaultState
    DefaultState abstract class, implementing State interface, extended by states
    DeleteDeliveryCommand
    Command that deletes a delivery from a delivery round Extends AbstractCommand abstract class Contains a typical day and a second delivery
    DeleteState
    State set when the user clicks on DeleteDeliveryButton Extends DefaultState abstract class
    DeliveryState
    Main state of the controller, basically set after executing or canceling a command Extends DefaultState abstract class
    InitState
    Initial state of the controller, basically set when the application is launched Extends DefaultState abstract class
    InverseCommand
    Command that inverse another command (set command.do = command.undo and conversely) Extends AbstractCommand abstract class Contains a command
    RequestState
    State set when the user loads a deliveries file, allow him to compute deliveries Extends DefaultState abstract class
    SwapDeliveriesCommand
    Command that swaps two deliveries in a delivery round Extends AbstractCommand abstract class Contains two deliveries
    SwapState
    State set when the user clicks on the SwapButton Extends DefaultState abstract class
